sourceMeaningMnemonic: The kanji and the radical are the same, so remembering the meaning of this kanji is as simple as making sure you know the radical for <radical>oneself</radical> first! If you know the radical, you know this kanji means <kanji>oneself</kanji> as well.
meaningInfo: Make sure you know those radicals, yo!
readingMnemonic: <kanji>Oneself</kanji>. Who only thinks of oneself? Every <ja><reading>子</reading></ja> (<ja>こ</ja>) in the world.
readingInfo: Kids can only think of oneself. Until a certain age, that's literally all they can care about.
